tr.td: The patient shows mildly decreased HbA1c and fasting glucose, suggesting possible hypoglycemia or tight glycemic control; other parameters including renal function, electrolytes, and calcium are within normal limits. No acute metabolic or renal disturbances are evident. Clinical correlation for hypoglycemia symptoms and medication review is recommended.
